    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "Code pointers:\r\nThis is the endpoint that build, sign and broadcast the transaction:\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/status-go/blob/57c7054dd2831386cbf1a67caf3ce25ad5d99691/services/wallet/api.go#L553-L556\r\n\r\nWe need to be able to separate the 3 actions.\r\n* Building the transactions should always be done by status-go\r\n* Signing the transaction can be done by status-go or keycard\r\n* Broadcasting the transaction still go via status-go\r\n\r\nFirst step is to identity this 3 logical flow and separate them so that they can be called individually\r\nOnce this is done we can start to work on the client to make the right call depending if it is an account managed by keycard or not",
